rden of Kubera, the god of wealth.\"","words":[{"d":"लङ्का","m":"Lanka"},{"d":"नानापतगसङ्घुष्टै:","m":"with flocks of bird of several kinds singing sweetly फलपुष्पोपगैः with charming flowers and fruits"},{"d":"शुभैः","m":"auspicious (gardens)"},{"d":"पुष्पितैः","m":"decorated with flowers"},{"d":"चित्ररथोपमैः","m":"like the Chaitraratha"},{"d":"वनैः","m":"gardens"},{"d":"शोभिता","m":"delighting."}]},{"v":12,"dev":"पश्यमत्तविहाङ्गानिप्रलीनभ्रमराणिच ।कोकिलाकुलषण्डानिदोधवीतिशिवोऽनिलः","trans":"\"You may see the trees shaking violently by the pleasant breeze, inhabited by proud birds, drunken honeybees and crowded with cuckoos and other birds (Rama said to Lakshmana).\"","words":[{"d":"शिवः","m":"pleasant"},{"d":"अनिलः","m":"breeze"},{"d":"मत्तविहङ्गानि","m":"inhabited by proud birds प्रलीनभ्रमराणीच drunken honeybees"},{"d":"कोकिलाकुलषण्डानि","m":"crowded with cuckoos and other birds"},{"d":"दोधवीति","m":"shaking violently"},{"d":"पश्य","m":"you may see (said Rama to Lakshmana)."}]},{"v":13,"dev":"इतिदाशरथीरामोलक्ष्मणंसमभाषत ।बलंचतद्वैविभजन् शास्त्रदृष्टेनकर्मणा","trans":"Dasaratha's son Rama thus talked to Lakshmana in that manner and asked to divide the task of the army in accordance with what is said in sastras.","words":[{"d":"दाशरथिः","m":"Dasaratha's"},{"d":"रामः","m":"Rama"},{"d":"इतिलक्ष्मणम्","m":"thus to Lakshmana"},{"d":"समभाषत","m":"talked"},{"d":"तद्वै","m":"in that manner"},{"d":"शास्त्रदृष्टेन","m":"in accordance with what is said in sastras"},{"d":"कर्मणा","m":"the task"},{"d":"बलं","m":"army"},{"d":"विभजच्छ","m":"and divide."}]},{"v":14,"dev":"शशासकपिसेनायांबलमादायवीर्यवान् ।अङ्गदस्सहनीलेनतिष्ठेदुरसिदुर्जयः","trans":"Let the valiant Angada who is difficult to win over, who is a terror to the enemies, take the army along with Nila and remain at the centre (of the army structure).","words":[{"d":"शशास","m":"terror for the enemies"},{"d":"वीर्यवान्","m":"valiant one"},{"d":"दुर्जयः","m":"one who is difficult to win over"},{"d":"अङ्गदः","m":"Angada"},{"d":"